<subSubSection id="2E806D45ACA5E4AE1198BB7738828C66" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5AA9F247C4B7FEEB7C5D80348FC97F07" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B666B29CEEBF32050A1BCF6CE5342DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The name is an anagram of the sister genus 
<taxonomicName id="05D9F58B5BFA8C147D63CA3BEAAF9C42" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orbamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orbamia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="58E41EF8D92E1867B93EAC7E4ED99D49" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Orbamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similarly to the anagram used by 
<bibRefCitation id="A2816FE0AA33F20EC65E6AD56692BA56" author="Herbulot, C" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin Mensuel Societe Linneenne de Lyon" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="216 - 221" refId="B12" refString="Herbulot, C, 1966. Nouveaux Geometridae du Sud-ouest de Madagascar. Bulletin Mensuel Societe Linneenne de Lyon 35: 216 - 221" title="Nouveaux Geometridae du Sud-ouest de Madagascar." volume="35" year="1966">Herbulot (1966)</bibRefCitation>
when transforming the name 
<taxonomicName id="8C611C03EF5915017C20EA6D1A0235A7" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Boarmia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boarmia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9DD231DEEA1D9DF1A771DE8C97948B5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Boarmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="A3C18AF933F010E0089E5D28C0BC3610" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Orbamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orbamia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CB3DA61C04153E5B827C8BF86FAF4097" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Orbamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CE0E7F2BF463086E2FD738BA875DF8C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="differential features">
<paragraph id="9CC0A69FFB119FD7F440DCEED28E13D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Differential features</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADEDC33E99BDA57CCBEB4637E0F492EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">(COI sequences, photographs of adults and their genitalia see https://dx.doi.org/10.5883/DS-ORBAMIA). Adult: Male antennae ciliate-fasciculate, female antennae filiform. Palpi of both sexes broad, bushy scaled, length in male 1.0, in female 1.5 times diameter of eye. Hind tibia of both sexes with two pairs of unequal spurs. Upperside of wings with inconspicuous, elongate discal spots, postmedial line of forewings sharp, strongly curved. Underside yellow, black terminal fascia conspicuous. Male genitalia: Uncus with three short sclerotised spines, lateral lobes below uncus swollen, saccus triangular, dorsal process of valva naked, with curved spinule at tip, aedeagus comparatively broad, with bundle of small cornuti at base, vesica condensed to a broad cornutus-like sclerite at tip. Female genitalia: Lamellae ante- and post-vaginalis sclerotised (elongate rhomboid), posteriorly rounded, ductus bursae sclerotised, long, helicoid, longitudinally furrowed, corpus bursae membranous, signum large, star-shaped.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB87E58121B9D6D6EF2E0071BD2E249F" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="genetic data and phylogeny">
<paragraph id="50D600AB8EA293A01868ED7AF3F7DC06" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Genetic data and phylogeny.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BE679C548444014C07B30E3674A55AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The maximum likelihood analysis of COI barcode data supports the monophyly of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="1957C51EFADBFD54820759C134CCBE55" authority="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba, 2020" authorityName="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Rabomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rabomia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F948B8FE28E94C62ABFBEBCCCDEC1670" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Rabomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. and sister group relationship with (
<taxonomicName id="D7BA43A187EB5A8B83C4D0EF6DD09A32" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Pycnostega" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pycnostega" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="31358EF806F99C28FD232E326B6916ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Pycnostega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="A3DA552509307F6841EFBBF754FFFC81" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Dorsifulcrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorsifulcrum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4F2A92A6A799BCDFE98825FCFF146FDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Dorsifulcrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. Table 
<tableCitation id="06C20C461B5E913965B903E764B6FE1E" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Barcode gap analysis of COI data of the genera Orbamia, Rabomia, and Morabia (https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5883 / DS-ORBAMIA), showing intraspecific variation (&quot; Mean Intra-Sp &quot; and &quot; Max. Intra-Sp. &quot;) and distances from Nearest Neighbour Species (&quot; NN &quot;)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5D9BF46CEBC36B6C506BFCB1111E5C75" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" tableUuid="5D9BF46CEBC36B6C506BFCB1111E5C75">1</tableCitation>
, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="782E48E40533EC16D217C322908CD031" captionStart="Figure 85" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 85. Maximum Likelihood Tree of COI data of the genera Orbamia, Rabomia, and Morabia, 50 Bootstrap Replications, Tamura-Nei model, uniform rates, built with Mega 6 software (Tamura et al. 2013; scale bar = 2 %), for original data see https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5883 / DS-ORBAMIA." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.929.50391.figure85" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/402627" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">85</figureCitation>
). However, phylogenies at genus level need to be considered with caution, when they are inferred from COI data. More research is needed to investigate the potential (re-) assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="249C4FB4A07C8557D81C7EE404D9F633" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Dorsifulcrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorsifulcrum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="59A5F42A392687330DF1A09E82DAFD5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Dorsifulcrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName id="95BE457D202B850B5E4D6D46A61DFB36" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1994" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassymini">Cassymini</taxonomicName>
after having been excluded from that tribe in 
<bibRefCitation id="9AA53C90FF8167C20DEA9414CD68B068" author="Brehm, G" journalOrPublisher="Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="457 - 486" refId="B4" refString="Brehm, G, Murillo-Ramos, L, Sihvonen, P, Hausmann, A, Schmidt, BC, Ounap, E, Moser, A, Moertter, R, Bolt, D, Bodner, F, Lindt, A, Parra, LE, Wahlberg, N, 2019. New World geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae): Molecular phylogeny, biogeography, taxonomic updates and description of 11 new tribes. Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny 77 (3): 457 - 486" title="New World geometrid moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae): Molecular phylogeny, biogeography, taxonomic updates and description of 11 new tribes." volume="77" year="2019">Brehm et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25B8C2D5CCCA0621C883B04B7BAE6046" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F6AE7C23D7EAA9F576AE6E47746CE2A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21E43895E8BF698A7136F355DE36E8F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
In some morphological features (e.g., female signum and ductus bursae) the genus 
<taxonomicName id="CA5881685D0D14E345F6615C5CAC1753" authority="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba, 2020" authorityName="Hausmann &amp; Tujuba" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Rabomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rabomia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C6BC38D11DC2C020AA1B237F98A8A08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Rabomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. is transitional to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="7BFC03DDA0480FF2C2A3348B9DF99D3D" authorityName="Herbulot" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Dorsifulcrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorsifulcrum" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1EE51D75D9F2B8C1C3C88BFE9C72667C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Dorsifulcrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Herbulot, 1979, but is genetically clustering separately, underside of wings with black fascia only in the terminal area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
